cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper deals with dense prediction problems in computer vision, which is a core topic in the computer vision community. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel module in neural networks, which is related to machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also experiments with video prediction tasks, which involves robotics and control, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.RO (Robotics) possible sub-categories.
